# Next.js, i18n, and Content

- Build with Next.js App Router conventions.
- All user-facing strings must be translatable with `next-intl` from day one.
- Do not hardcode UI copy in components/pages, except for temporary developer-only placeholders.
- Supported locales are fixed: `nl` (default), `fr`, `en`.
- New pages/components must include locale-aware copy keys and translations.
- No CMS integration unless explicitly requested.
- Keep site content local in `src/content` using JSON/MD when possible.
- Do not add remote content fetching unless explicitly requested.
